The paper deals with qualitative representations and constraint networks, which are commonly studied in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the algebraic foundations of these concepts, which falls under the category of mathematical logic (cs.LO). The computational complexity results presented in the paper suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-fields of data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
